		<![CDATA[From: jstettner@executecnia.com
To: rob.stettner@educatorstrust.net

Hi, Rob: Remember that your mom and dad are coming for dinner. I’m cooking. Would you like fish or meat? 

Jenny

--------------

From: rob.stettner@educatorstrust.net
To: jstettner@executecnia.com

Hey, Jenny: Thanks for cooking! I’m so busy at work right now. I’d like fish, but my mom and dad usually like meat, so how about a steak with a green bean salad and some potatoes? Something easy, OK? Don’t work too hard.

Love,
Rob

--------------

From: jstettner@executecnia.com
To: rob.stettner@educatorstrust.net

No problem. I’m going shopping for the meat after work. I think we have green beans and potatoes. Your mom likes fruit for dessert. Which fruit is her favorite?

-J

--------------
From: rob.stettner@educatorstrust.net
To: jstettner@executecnia.com

Don’t make dessert, Jen. Let me do that. I have a recipe for bananas in orange juice. It sounds delicious, and we have oranges and bananas in the fridge. OK?]]>
